  "sections": {
    "intro": "Hornetis one of theVekfromInto The Breach.",
    "Description": "Its appearance is a wasp that moves through the air to attack using its stinger ability.",
    "Strategy": "Compared to other early-game Vek, the Hornet's high mobility and immunity to drowning make it more slightly dangerous than the Scarab, but it is less threatening than the Scorpion, Leaper, or Firefly since Hornets can almost always be neutralized by a single Mech.\nTry to deploy your Mechs closer to the center of the board or to block chokepoints when Hornets are present, as their movement of 5 can otherwise allow them to slip out of reach into dangerous and unsolvable spots. Since its attack does not limit the target's mobility, it can be easily dodged and ignored if it targets a Mech. It should only be neutralized if it targets the grid, if it's starting to slip too far towards the back, or if no higher-threat Vek are present."
  },
  "full_text": "Hornet\nDetails\nHealth\n2\nMove\n5\nSystems\nStinger\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nStab the target for 1 damage.\nSpecial\nFlying\n: Flying units can move over any terrain tile.\nHornet\nis one of the\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nIts appearance is a wasp that moves through the air to attack using its stinger ability.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nCompared to other early-game Vek, the Hornet's high mobility and immunity to drowning make it more slightly dangerous than the Scarab, but it is less threatening than the Scorpion, Leaper, or Firefly since Hornets can almost always be neutralized by a single Mech.\nTry to deploy your Mechs closer to the center of the board or to block chokepoints when Hornets are present, as their movement of 5 can otherwise allow them to slip out of reach into dangerous and unsolvable spots. Since its attack does not limit the target's mobility, it can be easily dodged and ignored if it targets a Mech. It should only be neutralized if it targets the grid, if it's starting to slip too far towards the back, or if no higher-threat Vek are present.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
